itemListElement.name: Leavenworth Christmas Lighting Festival Tour from Seattle

name: Leavenworth Christmas Lighting Festival Tour from Seattle
description: Brimming with holiday magic and plenty of cheer, this is one event you will not want to miss! Hop on a deluxe motor coach departing from several locations around Seattle and enjoy a scenic ride across the Cascades to the Bavarian-themed town of Leavenworth. At dusk, gather for The Lighting Ceremony see the town come to life with more than half a million sparkling lights.

review.name: Clipper Vacations KNOWS how to make your trip to/from Leavenworth the easiest part of the day!
review.reviewBody:
The GREAT - Clipper Vacations Leavenworth tour bus. Comfortable bus - WITH A BATHROOM ONBOARD!! *This is a marvelous thing that makes the trip more comfortable - and saves significant time over companies who don't use buses that are equipped with facilities and have to make random rest stops. I've done a tour with a different company and it the travel to/from was nowhere near as easy and fun. 

The team - our driver Loy and guide Spencer were happy, fun, excited for us to have great time and took great care of their passengers from the moment we stepped on the bus until the moment we stepped off at the end of the day. Funny, cheerful, Christmas loving guides helped get everyone more excited for the day ahead. Thank you both!

Now to the reason for the trip:

Leavenworth Christmas Lighting - you know, that thing the sounds so "Christmasy" and fun that you go (again) even knowing that you will be part of a massive crowd competing for the same things, ability to go into the shops, get something to eat and drink, have some holiday fun...and then smooth together to see the lights switched on.

Leavenworth is a sweet little town that definitely looks like you walked into a classic Christmas village in Europe. Some very interesting shops, good restaurants, great distillery tasting room, a couple of great wine tasting rooms and loads of atmosphere.

IF you go - know it will be VERY crowded and space is at a premium. Space in stories, restaurants, tasting rooms - and especially restrooms (seriously there are very public restrooms available - even stores and restaurants will share 1 for the entire building, and though there is a strong history of how crowded the town gets there is NO restroom maintenance or trash pick up in town during the day leading to overflows of garbage everywhere by early afternoon. Leavenworth needs to manage this far better)

If you go - choose Clipper Vacations tour. And bring your holiday spirit and a lot of patience. It's fun, it's pretty but by the end of the day it's very nice to leave the hoardes behind and have a relaxing ride home!

review.name: Great Service
review.reviewBody: This will be our 2nd time to use Clipper Vacations to go to Leavenworth from Seattle in over 5 years. We know that it's going to be a long trip coming back to the city depending on the weather coming down through the passes, but this is the best way to experience the light show and the magic of Leavenworth without worrying about the traffic, parking etc and leave it to the great/trained bus drivers to get you through the trip. This year, the system refreshed online as we were booking the trip and it sent our pick up to Bellevue instead of Downtown Seattle. A call to their customer service fixed that within 10 minutes and wow, for promptness! I would recommend this company any time. I will post pictures soon!

review.name: Leavenworth destination is too successful
review.reviewBody: Clipper Vacations provided a good service too and from Leavenworth from Seattle on what was a long day. Having said that, we wouldn't recommend the experience. There were too many people in Leavenworth. There was limited space in shops and it was almost impossible to access food in hotels and restaurants. I think the experience may be better on any other night of the week in December and youd probably still get to see all the lights, just not a switching on of the lights. We didn't think the crowds, the cues and the lack of space was worth the cost of the tour. I'd like to stress though that Clipper Tours did a good job.

We boast a 5 minute drive to downtown; the space needle, Pike Place Market, the water front, Amazon and the Gates foundation.
